            <p:rationale>Decisions made from an enterprise-wide perspective have greater long-term value than decisions made from any particular organizational perspective. Maximum return-on-investment requires information management decisions to adhere to enterprise-wide goals and priorities. No minority group will detract from the benefit of the whole. Every change of information services or information management has to be evaluated in context of actual benefit to the enterprise as a whole.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>To achieve maximal enterprise-wide benefits, the criteria for planning and managing the information needs to be changed. A management of information must be considered from benefits to enterprise perspective. It will require a change not only of technology, business processes or rules, but also of organizational and personal approaches to information management within the enterprise.  As there can lot of requirements of the overall enterprise, priorities must be adjusted. A forum or committee of enterprise representatives should make these important decisions.
Priorities for application development, technology evolution, skill development should follow prioritization of enterprise needs.</p:implications>
